{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:31:50.035Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"I’ve got the shared bug now. Two local behaviors are suppressing exactly the warnings KiCad still emits:\n- `connected_pin_like_count_for_label()` counts peer labels as “pin-like” connections\n- `root_label_isolated()` blanket-suppresses a local label whenever a same-text hierarchical label exists\n\nBoth are too broad for the upstream cases we’re failing. I’m fixing those two shared rules now and then I’ll rerun the clustered hierarchy-label failures they should affect.","phase":"commentary","memory_citation":null}}
{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:31:50.035Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"I’ve got the shared bug now. Two local behaviors are suppressing exactly the warnings KiCad still emits:\n- `connected_pin_like_count_for_label()` counts peer labels as “pin-like” connections\n- `root_label_isolated()` blanket-suppresses a local label whenever a same-text hierarchical label exists\n\nBoth are too broad for the upstream cases we’re failing. I’m fixing those two shared rules now and then I’ll rerun the clustered hierarchy-label failures they should affect."}],"phase":"commentary"}}
