{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:32:52.804Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"I’ve got the remaining root suppression too. `top_level_hier_pins` proves that KiCad still emits `isolated_pin_label` for hierarchical labels connected only to sheet pins, so the sheet-pin special case in `root_label_isolated()` is also too aggressive. I’m removing that and adding direct pin-overlap counting for the no-wire hierarchical-label case.","phase":"commentary","memory_citation":null}}
{"timestamp":"2026-04-01T22:32:52.804Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"I’ve got the remaining root suppression too. `top_level_hier_pins` proves that KiCad still emits `isolated_pin_label` for hierarchical labels connected only to sheet pins, so the sheet-pin special case in `root_label_isolated()` is also too aggressive. I’m removing that and adding direct pin-overlap counting for the no-wire hierarchical-label case."}],"phase":"commentary"}}
