essage","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"Promoted `issue1768` into the maintained upstream-QA set and fixed the underlying parity bugs that blocked it.\n\nThe upstream-grounded changes are in [src/cmd/schematic/erc/rules/connectivity.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/rules/connectivity.rs), [src/cmd/schematic/erc/connectivity.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/connectivity.rs), and [src/schematic/render.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/schematic/render.rs). Concretely:\n- `duplicate_pins` now stays per symbol instance/unit, matching KiCad’s per-symbol duplicate-pin pass instead of collapsing shared pins across all units.\n- `different_unit_net` now follows the shared multi-unit conflict surface needed by upstream `issue1768`, including the auto-generated unconnected net naming used in the oracle.\n- helper power symbol lookup now resolves through the same embedded-symbol abstraction used elsewhere, which fixed rescue/project-local power symbols like `#PWR01`.\n- embedded pin parsing now respects `(hide yes)`, which fixed the remaining hidden-pin report mismatch.\n\nI added `issue1768` to [tests/cli_schematic_erc.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/tests/cli_schematic_erc.rs) and [manifest.json](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/tests/fixtures/erc_upstream_qa/manifest.json). The maintained upstream-QA exact set is now `85`. Verification I ran:\n- `cargo test --test cli_schematic_erc issue1768 -- --nocapture`\n- `cargo test --test cli_schematic_erc erc_parity_cases_manifest_is_well_formed -- --nocapture`\n- targeted parity checks for `duplicate_pins`, `different_unit_net`, `ground_pin_test_ok`, and `issue22286`\n\nI also moved into `issue9367` and traced the real blocker: our local model still drops most label-only/mixed-label wire groups before ERC, while upstream handles thos