symbol.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/rules/symbol.rs), and I recorded the residual state in [latest_comparison_summary.md](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/tests/fixtures/erc_upstream_qa/latest_comparison_summary.md).\n\nCurrent state after the fix:\n- `issue12814_2.kicad_sch` is behaviorally aligned on legacy power-symbol mismatch selection: only `#PWR05 [VCC]` remains, like upstream, but it is still not exact because the marker position is `1.4605` locally vs `1.46` in the oracle.\n- `issue12814_1.kicad_sch` regained the expected `VCC` mismatches on `#PWR01` and `#PWR04`, but it still differs on the real open bug: upstream emits one `power_pin_not_driven` item on `U1 Pin 1`, while local still splits that into `pin_not_driven` on pin 1 plus `power_pin_not_driven` on `U1 Pin 7 [GND]`.\n- `issue14494_subsheet1.kicad_sch` remains the next low-diff target; the remaining difference is still one extra local root `pin_not_connected` on hierarchical label `C`.\n\nVerification that passed:\n- `cargo test issue12814_power_symbol_mismatches_only_report_vcc -- --nocapture`\n- `cargo test embedded_power_vcc_signature_preserves_legacy_value_position_issue12814 -- --nocapture`\n- `cargo test -q --test cli_schematic_erc schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue12814_hierarchical_behavior -- --nocapture --test-threads=1`\n\nNo new exact upstream-QA case was promotable in this chunk, so the maintained exact count stays `109`."}],"phase":"final_answer"},{"type":"message","role":"user","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"Keep going. Always keep implementation and abstractions grounded to upstream code. You are an\n  autonomus agent, please keep working until ERC is closed. Do not stop if you still have a full\n  upstream-qa parity merge request is ready. Do not stop after each case."}]},{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"Promoted `issue13212.kicad_sch` into the maintained upstream-QA exact set. The maintained exact count is now `110`.\n\nThe upstream-grounded fix is in [hierarchy.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/rules/hierarchy.rs). I added root-sheet projection for isolated child `global_label`s only when the same global label text is not already present on the parent sheet. That matches the upstream `issue13212` behavior from [test_erc_global_labels.cpp](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/kicad/qa/tests/eeschema/erc/test_erc_global_labels.cpp): the full project now reports the missing root `isolated_pin_label` for `Global Label 'LABEL_3'`, while still suppressing the duplicate-text `LABEL_2` case. I added the maintained exact regression in [tests/cli_schematic_erc.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/tests/cli_schematic_erc.rs) and the manifest entry in [manifest.json](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/tests/fixtures/erc_upstream_qa/manifest.json).\n\nVerification that passed:\n- `cargo test -q --test cli_schematic_erc schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue13212_fixture -- --nocapture --test-threads=1`\n- `cargo test -q --test cli_schematic_erc schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue13212_subsheet_1_fixture -- --nocapture --test-threads=1`\n- `cargo test -q --test cli_schematic_erc schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue13212_subsheet_2_fixture -- --nocapture --test-threads=1`\n- `cargo test -q --test cli_schematic_erc erc_parity_cases_manifest_is_well_formed -- --nocapture --test-threads=1`\n\nI also checked one candidate promotion and kept it out: `spice_netlists/legacy_rectifier/legacy_rectifier.kicad_sch` looked exact from the stale frontier but still fails narrow exact verification on a missing `rectifier_schlib:R` `lib_symbol_mismatch`, so I reverted that attempted promotion instead of leaving stale manifest churn. The next live low-diff target is `issue20173/Kicad 9 - multi channel test.kicad_sch`, which is currently down to three missing upstream `wire_d