r on the best visible non-power-symbol pin when possible.\n\nLocal changes:\n- In [render.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/schematic/render.rs), placed symbols now retain `annotated_on_current_sheet`, and pin nodes carry `drives_net` based on KiCad’s driver eligibility model instead of assuming every placed pin can drive.\n- In [connectivity.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/connectivity.rs) and [root.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/rules/root.rs), `wire_dangling` now keys off driver-like attachment instead of raw attachment, which is what closed `issue20173/Kicad 9 - multi channel test.kicad_sch`.\n- In [connectivity.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/rules/connectivity.rs) and [root.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/rules/root.rs), mixed input/power-input nets now follow the upstream power-net rule, which closed `issue12814_1.kicad_sch`.\n- I added parser regressions in [render.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/schematic/render.rs), added the exact case in [cli_schematic_erc.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/tests/cli_schematic_erc.rs), and promoted it in [manifest.json](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/tests/fixtures/erc_upstream_qa/manifest.json).\n\nVerification that passed:\n- `cargo test -q --test cli_schematic_erc schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue20173_fixture -- --nocapture --test-threads=1`\n- `cargo test -q --test cli_schematic_erc schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue12814_1_fixture -- --nocapture --test-threads=1`\n- `cargo test -q --test cli_schematic_erc schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue12814_2_fixture -- --nocapture --test-threads=1`\n- `cargo test -q --test cli_schematic_erc schematic_erc_matches_upstream_issue18092_fixture -- --nocapture --test-threads=1