e a full\n  upstream-qa parity merge request is ready. Do not stop after each case."}]},{"type":"message","role":"user","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"Keep going"}]},{"type":"message","role":"user","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"Keep going. Always keep implementation and abstractions grounded to upstream code. You are an\n  autonomus agent, please keep working until ERC is closed. Do not stop if you still have a full\n  upstream-qa parity merge request is ready. Do not stop after each case.Keep going"}]},{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"Promoted `issue17870.kicad_sch` into the maintained upstream-QA exact set. The maintained exact count is now `129`.\n\nThe upstream grounding stayed on KiCad’s no-connect and subgraph logic in [connection_graph.cpp](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/kicad/eeschema/connection_graph.cpp) and the four-way regression in [test_erc_four_way.cpp](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/kicad/qa/tests/eeschema/erc/test_erc_four_way.cpp). The local fixes are in [connectivity.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/src/cmd/schematic/erc/rules/connectivity.rs):\n- `pin_not_connected` now matches KiCad’s power-symbol handling more closely: multiple non-stacked pins only count as “other connections” for non-power symbols, and helper power groups with real attached graphical items are not spuriously reported as dangling.\n- `bus_to_net_conflict` now has a KiCad-shaped mixed subgraph path for nets that bridge wire and bus items through the same logical net, and it suppresses the redundant direct crossing when that broader mixed-net conflict exists.\n\nI added the maintained exact regression in [tests/cli_schematic_erc.rs](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/tests/cli_schematic_erc.rs) and the manifest entry in [manifest.json](/Users/Daniel/Desktop/modular/tools/ki-erc-refactor-wt/tests/fixtures/erc_upstream_qa/manifest.json).\n\nVerification that passed:\n- `cargo test -q --test